{
  "design_notes": "A well-structured Hard chart designed for a 4-panel dance pad. The intro starts with basic onbeats to map the quiet synth lines. S1 kicks in with a solid sequence of hold notes mirroring the long sustained vocals and bass modulations. The buildup (S2/S3) escalates into a stream of 8th and 16th taps, using zigzag and drifting motions to encourage a comfortable physical flow. The drop (S4) pushes the difficulty with denser rhythmic taps and accent-oriented jumps on main snare hits. S6 and S8 offer a satisfying physical workout through alternating quick holds and stream runs, utilizing the moderate crossover limit with sweeping patterns. S14 drives home the climax of the track with dense patterns that cleanly wrap up into a rhythmic outro of slow taps on the final beats.",
